claim.claim-text:
A solid ion conductor comprising:
a garnet-type oxide represented by Formula 1 below:



         <Formula 1>     L5+xE3(Mez,M2-z)Od



wherein L is at least one of a monovalent cation and a divalent cation, and a part of or all of L is Li;

E is a trivalent cation;

Me and M are each independently a trivalent, tetravalent, pentavalent, or hexavalent cation;

0<x≤3, 0≤z<2, and 0<d≤12; and

O is partially or totally substituted with at least one of a pentavalent anion, a hexavalent anion, and a heptavalent anion.

The solid ion conductor of claim 1, wherein the garnet-type oxide of Formula 1 is represented by Formula 2 below:



         <Formula 2>     L5+x+2y(Dy,E3-y)(Mez, M2-z)Od



wherein L is at least one of a monovalent cation and a divalent cation, and a part of or all of L is Li;

D is a monovalent cation;

E is a trivalent cation;

Me and M are each independently a trivalent, tetravalent, pentavalent, or hexavalent cation;

0<x+2y≤3, 0<y≤0.5, 0≤z<2, and 0<d≤12; and

O is partially or totally substituted with at least one of a pentavalent anion, a hexavalent anion, and a heptavalent anion.

The solid ion conductor of claim 4, wherein the garnet-type oxide of Formula 2 is represented by Formula 3:



         <Formula 3>     L5+x+2y(Dy,La3-y)(Mez,Zr2-z)Od



wherein L is at least one of a monovalent cation and a divalent cation, and a part of or all of L is Li;

D is a monovalent cation;

Me is a trivalent, tetravalent, pentavalent, or hexavalent cation;

0<x+2y≤3, 0<y≤0.5, 0≤z<2, and 0<d≤12; and

O is partially or totally substituted with at least one of a pentavalent anion, a hexavalent anion, and a heptavalent anion.
